snippet.textDisplay: I get the feeling the first team is burnt out. We missed El Hamid today too. Minor but his pace and awareness is awesome. I have thought recently that we lacked depth though the middle but Ntcham has proven himself to be good cover for Scott Brown. I now believe that in January we need an additional centre back, right winger, attacking midfielder and striker but January isn't as easy as the Summer to get good signings. We've underestimated Rangers depth and physical strength. Team morale is one thing but now we need less joviality and a very serious mindset. Rangers mean business and we seriously need to too. We lack leadership and also, maybe Greg Taylor should get a run in the first team?

snippet.textDisplay: Lets not get too anxious. At 1-1 if we score then we could have won this and been 8 clear with Gerrard finishes at Rangers so we were 1 goal from that outcome. So now Rangers will be heralded as the having risen fully from the dead, but they were fighting for Gerards Job today, their own Rangers careers, and the 9-in-a-row essentially plus the acrimony of having lost the cup final in unfortunate circumstances. All of that was on the line for them today. Rangers had an overwhelming set of motivating factors and it shone through as they won most of the on-pitch battles today. Lennon also has to have more respect for them and match them up more in midfield as they stifled us in the middle and needs to make more judicious use of our emerging talents such as Frimpong and Johnston as today was a day for experiences battle-hard footballers. I have always thought the Jan transfer window will decide this league, but Gerrard has a lot of pulling power so I would not rule out him landing a couple of big names on loan, but we can counteract that with by signing the following 3 players in my view - CF, DEFMid, and another Centre back. We have had a good first half season, and we are a good team, and we have time to fix this and take the Rangers challenge with the seriousness it deserves. Hail, Hail

snippet.textDisplay:
Let's be brutally honest now. There is no need for any panic here, We were very poor today and Rangers got the luck they needed and did enough to win. The facts are we missed a pen and had 2 cleared off the line, they had Fredo up top (thank god) otherwise it could have been much worse for us. Kent took his goal really well but did not much else. So all in all we are still top we have nothing to fear and Gerrard reaction today sums it up they are a bang average side who got a MASSIVE result today. It looked like some of the hoops players heads were already in Dubai. It's a law of averages, I think this loss comes at the perfect time as it should then give us the shake we need to kick on from here. A couple of quality additions in Jan, re group and we go again for the QuadTreble.
Hail Hail 🍀

snippet.textDisplay: no kneejerk reactions from me.think we need to assess the year and conclude its been good, very good, lenny has done very well, steadied the ship when he came in, guided us to the title when it could have slipped away, won the cup, then the europa league was a success as we topped the group, then won the league cup, also won first old firm game of season, but todays result has been coming, no surprise today, i dont blame lenny, rangers have improved and bought a squad they cant afford or sustain, but that dosent matter, we need to be prepared to beat who they put out and we didnt, still no major harm done, were still 2 points ahead although in reality rangers will win the game in hand, but title is still in our hands. we cant write todays result off as just a noisy neighbour winning the odd game, just like last seasons old firm defeat in december which ultimately meant nothing to them in the long run, rangers will do anything to stop us doing 10, even if it means them needing £10 million of someone elses money every year, we need to teach this financial basket case once and for all, over to you peter lawell, give lenny the cash to improve the squad in january, even if it means taking a financial risk in the short term. anyway im dissapointed today but always happy to support the worlds most succesful unliquidated club, which always pays its bills and dosent shaft the taxman, hail hail, ps. well done sevco for todays result. keep spending and hope yous snuff it like oldco rangers did.

snippet.textDisplay: Too many lightweights in the team. We missed Elyonoussi, he’d been ripping it up before his injury. Mikey Johnston is fine when it comes to playing the lesser sides, but he’s been anonymous when he’s played against Rangers. Forrest & even Christie haven’t turned up yet again, or maybe they’re just not good enough. Scott Brown worked his socks off, but we need more presence & creativity in midfield, because Rangers took complete control & stopped us from creating anything. How many times did Frimpong try to run at Rangers, but we had no movement off the ball for him. We deserved nothing from this game & unless we can bring in a couple of real quality players in January, I fear the title is going next door. Thank heavens that Morelos cannot score against us or we’d have been hammered.

snippet.textDisplay:
We needed a performance today, and there just wasn't one. There were a couple decent spells, but overall very poor today.

We needed to come out and hammer them, we could've, but there were too many pedestrians on the park. And when the subs came on, you could see they were not up for it either.

You can't win them all, sure, but i expected a good show, one game before the winter break.

Gonna have to play alot harder to wrap up the title. Could've pretty much sewn it up today with a bit of grit.

snippet.textDisplay:
We have accumulated a powderpuff team. Simple as that. First 30 minutes brown was single handedly competing against a 5 man midfield!! Boli is a million miles from Celtic quality. Forrest is a coward and heart of a mouse, cowards out of every challenge and hides from the ball, automatically one man down. Christie was abysmal, why isn’t our striker taking the penalty? Johnston posted missing but tried. Frimpong left out to dry, 19 year old being passed the ball and expected to do magic!! It reeks of arrogance from Lennon, playing exactly the same formation and exactly the same strategy against a team
Who dominated in the last game. Not changing this until 65mins when blatantly not working. This 9 in a row is in major jeopardy.

We need physical, hard players who will stand up to the physicality of sevco. Forrest, Johnston, Christie, boli, frimpong, do not have the physical aspect of their game to compete in old firm. You need to earn the right to play, Celtic aren’t earning the right to play. Ultimately, comes down to mismanagement and poor investment from the top. If we lose the league lawwells and Lennon legacy will be in tatters and fans will not forgive them
